ðŸ§  ADX Structure (3 lines)
+DI (Positive Directional Indicator) â€“ Buyers control

âˆ’DI (Negative Directional Indicator) â€“ Sellers control

ADX â€“ The average difference between +DI and -DI over time

ADX á€€á€­á€¯ á€™á€­á€™á€­á€›á€½á€±á€¸á€á€»á€šá€ºá€á€²á€· period (á€¥á€•á€™á€¬ 14) á€•á€±á€«á€ºá€™á€°á€á€Šá€ºá€•á€¼á€®á€¸ +DI á€”á€²á€· âˆ’DI á€á€½á€±á€›á€²á€· divergence á€€á€­á€¯ smooth average á€œá€¯á€•á€ºá€á€¬á€–á€¼á€…á€ºá€á€šá€ºá‹

ðŸ§® Calculation Summary
True Range (TR) = max(high - low, abs(high - prev close), abs(low - prev close))

+DM / -DM (Directional Movement) = directional price change

Smooth these values over n-period (default 14)

Calculate +DI / -DI

diff
Copy
Edit
+DI = 100 * (Smoothed +DM / ATR)
-DI = 100 * (Smoothed -DM / ATR)
DX = 100 * |(+DI - -DI)| / (+DI + -DI)

ADX = EMA of DX over time (default 14)

ðŸ“ˆ Signal Usage
âœ… Trending Market Confirmation
ADX > 25 â†’ trending market

ADX rising â†’ trend getting stronger

ADX falling â†’ trend weakening (may enter consolidation)

âœ… Combine with DI
+DI > -DI and ADX rising â†’ strong uptrend

-DI > +DI and ADX rising â†’ strong downtrend

ADX falling â†’ avoid trend-following strategies

âœ… Strategy Use Case
text
Copy
Edit
IF (ADX > 25 AND +DI > -DI) THEN
   BUY signal (strong uptrend)
ELSE IF (ADX > 25 AND -DI > +DI) THEN
   SELL signal (strong downtrend)
ELSE
   SIDEWAYS â†’ skip or range strategy


